<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Explanatory_notes">Explanatory notes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Leon_P._Miller&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Explanatory notes"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<div class="reflist reflist-lower-alpha">
<div class="mw-references-wrap"><ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-fn1-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-fn1_2-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-fn1_2-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">The name of the Criminal Court of McDowell County was changed to the Intermediate Court of McDowell County following an act of the <a href="/wiki/West_Virginia_Legislature" title="West Virginia Legislature">West Virginia Legislature</a> in 1971.<sup id="cite_ref-Myers_1971_380_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Myers_1971_380-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-fn2-22"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-fn2_22-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">According to the <i>West Virginia Blue Book</i>, Miller served on the Welch city council in 1944,<sup id="cite_ref-Watkins_1944_544_17-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Watkins_1944_544-17">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup> 1945,<sup id="cite_ref-Myers_1945_544_18-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Myers_1945_544-18">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup> 1946,<sup id="cite_ref-Myers_1946_560_19-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Myers_1946_560-19">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup> 1947,<sup id="cite_ref-Myers_1947_640_20-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Myers_1947_640-20">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup> and 1948.<sup id="cite_ref-Myers_1948_554_21-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Myers_1948_554-21">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-fn3-45"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-fn3_45-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">A sticker vote is a sticker affixed to a ballot with a candidate's name and office printed on it.<sup id="cite_ref-WVSOS_2014_3–4_44-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-WVSOS_2014_3–4-44">&#91;42&#93;</a></sup></span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
